<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>jump in the lake • take the plunge</xh5><p> <i>jump in the lake</i>—(also: go jump in the lake) is used to rudely tell a person to go away (and stop being annoying): After a while, our exchange turned hostile and I told him to <u>jump in the lake</u>.</p><p> <i>take the plunge—</i>take a decisive step (especially getting married); venture to do smth. risky: You may <u>take the plunge</u> and start your own firm, or join a large company.</p> </entry>
